> When it comes to chicken, we're always looking for two things: golden crackly skin and juicy, flavorful meat. Enter: these roasted chicken legs. They're all that and then some—the "some" being a sticky BBQ glaze that really takes 'em above and beyond. They're served with green beans, plus our new favorite spud side: fingerling potatoes that are roasted, smashed to create craggy edges, and roasted again with cheese until perfectly crispy, melty, and golden. Ready to get a LEG up on dinnertime?

== Chicken and Potatoes ==

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Line a #baking sheet{} with foil. Wash and dry produce (except green beans).

Pat @chicken legs{16%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}. Season all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}; drizzle each piece with @olive oil{2%teaspoon} and rub to coat. Place skin sides up on one side of prepared sheet.

Toss @fingerling potatoes{12%ounce} on empty side with a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%teaspoon}, salt, and pepper. Roast on top rack for ~{20%minutes} (you'll add more to the sheet then).

-- 4 SERVINGS: Adjust racks to top and middle positions. Spread chicken out across prepared sheet and toss potatoes on a separate, unlined sheet; roast chicken on top rack and potatoes on middle rack.

Once chicken and potatoes have roasted ~{20%minutes}, remove sheet from oven.

Carefully flatten potatoes with a #spatula{} or heavy cup. Season with salt and pepper, then top with @Monterey Jack cheese{1/4%cup}.

Brush chicken with half the @BBQ sauce{4%tablespoon} (save the rest for serving).

Return to top rack until chicken is cooked through, potatoes are slightly crispy, and cheese has melted, ~{8-12%minutes} more.

> TIP: Push the potatoes closer together for more cheese coverage!

== Green Beans ==

When chicken and potatoes are almost done, pierce @green beans{6%ounce} bag with a #fork{}; place bag on a #plate{}. Microwave until tender, ~{1-2%minutes}.

> TIP: No microwave? No problem! Steam beans in a small pot with a splash of water until just tender, 5-7 minutes.

== To Serve ==

Divide chicken, potatoes, and green beans between plates. Season green beans with salt and pepper. Top potatoes with @smoky red pepper crema{2%tablespoon} and serve with remaining BBQ sauce on the side for dipping.